body:
We've been working on some ideas and including everyone with @fvictorio.

This is a preliminary version of how this would work, and how the config would look like.

```js
// 1. Everything will be compiled with 0.5.5 and 0.6.1 as defined in
// the compilersarray.
//
// 2. If there's a file which can't be compiled with 0.5.5 nor 0.6.1, 
// the compilation process will fail.
//
// 3. If a file can be compiled with either version it will be compiled
// using the max possible version.
//
// 4. The file contracts/Fool.sol will be compiled using 0.5.5 with 
// different settings.
//
// 5. The final version would have less-verbose ways to set it up.
"solidity": {
  "compilers": [
     { 
        "version": "0.5.5",
        "settings": {
          "optimizer": { "enabled": false}
        }
     },
     { 
        "version": "0.6.1",
        "settings": {
          "optimizer": { "enabled": true}
        }
     }
  ],
  "overrides": {
    "contracts/Foo.sol": {
       "version": "0.5.5"
       "settings": {
          "optimizer": { "enabled": true, runs: 1000 }
       }
    }
  }
}
```

Would something like this cover your use-case, @justinjmoses ?

Please, note that this is work in progress. Nothing is settled yet. Any feedback is wellcome.

@K-Ho Would a path to the solc js "binary" be enough? 

Something like:

```js
     { 
        "version": "0.5.5",
        "solcJs": "./custom-compilers/solidity-ovm-0.5.5.js",
        "settings": {
          "optimizer": { "enabled": false}
        }
     },
```
